[{"id":39198,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>For series combination,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5b53447a-33fb-4312-9de6-6a4eddc526c0-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 75px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>C</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>C</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><menclose notation=\"box\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></menclose></math></p><p>For parallel combination,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a838769a-6cfb-422b-bd36-3b0b28d0541f-image.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 117px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39172,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>130</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>260</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>585</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/324a3f42-35de-467c-b85c-4dbdad4488bb-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p>As we know,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></math></p><p>Here all capacitors are connected in series.</p><p>Thus, equivalent capacitance is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mn>13</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, charge&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mn>13</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>.</p><p>As the capacitors are connected in series, charge on each capacitor wil be same.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39123,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$1$","$1.33$","$0.66$","$1.50$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\frac{\\mathrm{A} \\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{o}}}{\\mathrm{d}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{A} \\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{o}}}{\\left(0.2+\\frac{\\mathrm{d}}{\\mathrm{k}}\\right)} \\\\ & 0.6=0.2+\\frac{0.6}{\\mathrm{k}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{k}=\\frac{3}{2}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39250,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["At <math> <mrow> <mtext>t</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>&tau;</mi> <mtext>,&nbsp; q</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>CV&nbsp;</mtext> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>-</mo> <msup> <mtext>e</mtext> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math>","At <math> <mrow> <mtext>t</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi>&#964;</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mtext>,&#160; q</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>CV&#160;</mtext> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>-</mo> <msup> <mtext>e</mtext> <mn>-1</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math>","Work done by the battery is half of the energy dissipated in the resistor","<math><mrow><mtext>At t</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mi>&tau;</mi> <mtext>,&nbsp; q</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>CV</mtext> <mo>/</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math> <mrow> <mtext>q</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>CV</mtext> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>-</mo> <msup> <mtext>e</mtext> <mrow> <mtext>t</mtext> <mo>/</mo> <mi>&tau;</mi> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math><br />&nbsp;<br />At <math> <mrow> <mtext>t</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>&tau;</mi> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mtext>q</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>CV</mtext> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>-</mo> <msup> <mtext>e</mtext> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (07 Apr)","image":null},{"id":39095,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$2.2$","$2.0$","$2.1$","$2.4$"],"answer":0,"solution":"From the given circuit diagram, the battery is connected such that its positive terminal is upwards. This means the current will flow in the clockwise direction during the charging of the capacitor.<br><br>In the parallel combination of the two diodes, the left diode is pointing downwards (in the direction of the current) and will be forward-biased. The right diode is pointing upwards (opposite to the current) and will be reverse-biased.<br><br>The reverse-biased diode offers infinite resistance and acts as an open circuit. The forward-biased diode offers a resistance of $10\\ \\Omega$.<br><br>The total equivalent resistance of the circuit is the sum of the resistor $R$ and the resistance of the forward-biased diode:<br>$R_{eq} = 100\\ \\Omega + 10\\ \\Omega = 110\\ \\Omega$<br><br>The time constant $\\tau$ of the $RC$ circuit is given by:<br>$\\tau = R_{eq}C$<br>$\\tau = 110 \\times 20 \\times 10^{-6}\\ \\text{s}$<br>$\\tau = 2200 \\times 10^{-6}\\ \\text{s} = 2.2 \\times 10^{-3}\\ \\text{s}$<br><br>Comparing this with the given time constant $\\alpha \\times 10^{-3}\\ \\text{s}$, we get:<br>$\\alpha = 2.2$<br><br>Answer: $2.2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39160,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>As the given capacitors are in parallel combination, therefore,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></math></p><p>Hence, charge flown through the switch<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39232,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>nC</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>nC</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>nC</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>nC</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"Induced charge on the dielectric,<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>k</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>20</mn><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1.2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>nC</mi></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (08 Apr)","image":null},{"id":39175,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3e83a4dc-9cdf-4440-8382-7b602355fa3e-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 174px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;Before the metal sheet is inserted, capacitance is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>A</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math>.</p><p>After the sheet is inserted, the system is equivalent to two capacitors in series, each of capacitance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>C</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>A</mi></mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>C</mi></math>.<br />The equivalent capacity is now <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>C</mi></math>.</p><p>The ratio is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39205,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>450</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>590</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>650</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>C</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bacaa7ad-9534-4495-8512-ce585a148834-image.png\" style=\"width: 291px; height: 228px;\" /></p><p>Applying&nbsp;Kirchoff&#39;s law we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>750</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>160</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>750</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>590</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39118,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7KCw4RhEnwfTvBPZCb_cZlPSWZuZvMvijD7jtGKHU9E.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\n\n\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{i}=\\left(\\frac{5}{25}\\right) \\\\ & \\mathrm{Q}=\\mathrm{CV} \\\\ & \\mathrm{Q}=\\left(8 \\times 10^{-6}\\right)\\left(\\frac{5}{25} \\times 10\\right) \\\\ & \\mathrm{Q}=\\left(\\frac{8 \\times 5 \\times 10^{-2}}{25}\\right)=16 \\mu \\mathrm{C}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39108,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/l8TLU8DE1DjuQVIVXdp4vXCdLC7vPkh4b0wA_8RJHVY.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>Redrawing<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ytMHLMa0570eN8IclNNkqniKn6CLSAVn0TNaW5uoW1I.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>$\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{eq}}=4 \\mathrm{C}=64$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39208,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>∈</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>α</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>∈</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>α</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>∈</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>α</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>∈</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>α</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c1f0d70f-e9db-46ff-8662-e56ae3853df3-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 182px;\" /><br /><math><mi>d</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#8712;</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi></mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#8712;</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow></mfrac><msubsup><mrow><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>I</mi><mi>n</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msubsup></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#8712;</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>I</mi><mi>n</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#945;</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#8776;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#8712;</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#945;</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39199,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cbf13310-bbcd-4d47-8167-3813e7da5d77-image.png\" style=\"width: 295px; height: 170px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d037371-cd52-4733-aa97-697638d7ce93-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 171px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9793b169-e1f8-4e8b-8bcb-ed6f757b3a8e-image.png\" style=\"width: 297px; height: 180px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d037371-cd52-4733-aa97-697638d7ce93-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 171px;\" />&nbsp;"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3d951631-ed03-464f-a5af-0aaccec39f57-image.png\" style=\"width: 295px; height: 170px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>When first pulse is applied the potential across capacitor is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>When no pulse is applied, capacitor will discharge like&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn><mo>&#39;</mo></msubsup><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;when again, second pulse is applied&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Using all three equations the correct graph is :</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39106,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{Q}_{\\mathrm{in}}=\\mathrm{Q}\\left(1-\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{~K}}\\right) \\\\ & 4 \\times 10^{-6}=5 \\times 10^{-6}\\left(1-\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{~K}}\\right) \\\\ & 1-\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{~K}}=\\frac{4}{5} \\\\ & \\mathrm{~K}=5\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39183,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math>","zero"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b999745a-b961-4914-8c47-c8be97982016-image.png\" style=\"width: 317px; height: 218px;\" /></p><p>Using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8756;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;Volt</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>q</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39217,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6278915c-23c9-47c7-b784-54061942f701-image7.png\"> <br/>Charge inside capacitor <math><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>  <br/><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> volt","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39092,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$5$","$\\dfrac{5}{2}$","$\\dfrac{7}{2}$","$\\dfrac{9}{2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Initial energy of the charged sphere is given by:<br><br>$U_i = \\dfrac{1}{2} C V^2$<br><br>$U_i = \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 100 \\times 10^{-12} \\times (100)^2 = 5 \\times 10^{-7}$ J<br><br>When the identical uncharged sphere is brought in contact, the charge is shared equally and the common potential becomes:<br><br>$V' = \\dfrac{V}{2} = 50$ V<br><br>Final total energy of the two spheres is:<br><br>$U_f = 2 \\times \\left( \\dfrac{1}{2} C V'^2 \\right) = C V'^2$<br><br>$U_f = 100 \\times 10^{-12} \\times (50)^2 = 2.5 \\times 10^{-7}$ J<br><br>Change in energy is the loss of energy during charge sharing:<br><br>$\\Delta U = U_i - U_f = 5 \\times 10^{-7} - 2.5 \\times 10^{-7} = 2.5 \\times 10^{-7}$ J<br><br>$\\Delta U = \\dfrac{5}{2} \\times 10^{-7}$ J<br><br>Comparing with $\\alpha \\times 10^{-7}$ J, we get $\\alpha = \\dfrac{5}{2}$.<br><br>Answer: $\\dfrac{5}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39255,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["No charge flows in (a) but charge flows from $R$ to $L$ in (b)","Charges flow from $L$ to $R$ in both (a) and (b)","Charges flow from $R$ to $L$ in (a) and from $L$ to $R$ in (b)","No charge flows in (a) but charge flows from $L$ to $R$ in (b)"],"answer":2,"solution":"Charge (or current) always flows from higher potential to lower potential.\nPotential $=\\frac{\\text { Charge }}{\\text { Capacitance }}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":39122,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$\\frac{13 \\epsilon_o A}{17 d}$","$\\frac{11 \\epsilon_{\\mathrm{o}} \\mathrm{A}}{18 \\mathrm{~d}}$","$\\frac{18 \\epsilon_{\\mathrm{o}} \\mathrm{A}}{11 \\mathrm{~d}}$","$\\frac{11 \\epsilon_{\\mathrm{o}} \\mathrm{A}}{20 \\mathrm{~d}}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"All capacitor are in parallel combination.\nAlso effective area is common area only\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\Rightarrow C_{\\text {eq }}=C_1+C_2+C_3 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow C_{\\text {eq }}=\\frac{A \\varepsilon_0}{3 d}+\\frac{A \\varepsilon_0}{3(2 d)}+\\frac{A \\varepsilon_0}{3(3 d)} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow C_{\\text {eq }}=\\frac{A \\varepsilon_0}{3}\\left(\\frac{11}{6 d}\\right) \\\\ & \\Rightarrow C_{\\text {eq }}=\\frac{11 A \\varepsilon_0}{18 d}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39263,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$(n-1) C$","$(n+1) C$","$C$","$nC$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$C_{e q}=(n-1) C(\\because$ all capacitors are in parallel $)$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":39219,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>μ</mi><mi>F</mi></math>","<math><mn>4</mn><mi> </mi><mi>μ</mi><mi>F</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>11</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>F</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>μ</mi><mi>F</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Let us take the equivalent circuit one by one.<br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bbb088c0-aedb-467b-8e0d-18b62e08c1ff-image.png\" style=\"width: 403px; height: 200px;\" /><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f424bc2a-fe45-482c-bacf-9efca9308b2e-image.png\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/efd508c8-8074-4453-b9a8-8509697dcedf-image.png\" /><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfrac></math> = 0.5 <math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>F</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39193,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6b1cea98-d7e1-4faf-a313-1d2b4c1dd441-image.png\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 263px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39194,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pJ</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>C</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1008</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pJ</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>f</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1008</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mi>pJ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>144</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pJ</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8757;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Mechanical energy<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>U</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1008</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>144</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>864</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pJ</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39138,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The capacitor works as an open circuit in the given configuration.</p><p>The potential difference between the two plates of the capacitor will be the difference across the resistors having resistances&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math>.</p><p>Hence, the potential difference&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;across the capacitor can be calculated as follows:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>V</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the energy stored in the capacitor is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>C</mi><mo>(</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>V</mi><mrow><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></mrow></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (1) to calculate the required energy stored.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>U</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;J</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39116,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$\\varepsilon_0 \\mathrm{E}^2 \\mathrm{Ad}$","$\\frac{1}{2} \\varepsilon_0 \\mathrm{E}^2 \\mathrm{Ad}$","$\\frac{1}{4} \\varepsilon_0 \\mathrm{E}^2 \\mathrm{Ad}$","$\\frac{3}{4} \\varepsilon_0 \\mathrm{E}^2 \\mathrm{Ad}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"We know energy density\n$\\rho_{\\mathrm{av}}=\\frac{1}{2} \\varepsilon_0 E^2$\nSo potential energy $=\\rho_{a v} \\times$ Volume\n$\\Rightarrow \\text { P.E. }=\\frac{1}{2} \\varepsilon_0 E^2 A d$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39260,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$1$","$2$","$\\frac{1}{4}$","$\\frac{1}{2}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\frac{\\frac{1}{2} q v}{q v}=\\frac{1}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":39215,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>V</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"i)<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e6c49185-b276-4919-aff7-3b17c6675067-image.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 116px;\" /><br />ii) Battery disconnected after full charge,<br />Total charge of the system,<br /><math><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/11796ce8-839a-4c4a-a8c2-779c6256c99d-image.png\" style=\"width: 186px; height: 100px;\" /><br />iii) Inserting dielectric of constant <math><mi>K</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4687a8a8-0963-4a1f-8cf8-bf9d953439be-image.png\" style=\"width: 201px; height: 100px;\" /><br />Common potential, <math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39222,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["$-12 \\mu \\mathrm{C}$","$+12 \\mu \\mathrm{C}$","$-18 \\mu \\mathrm{C}$","$+18 \\mu \\mathrm{C}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hQlrAEfPQGJRsolRyyhb7HSrTP0RMCpjxI0ajRABDFE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\r\n\r\nAs given in the figure, $6 \\mu \\mathrm{F}$ and $4 \\mu \\mathrm{F}$ are in parallel. Now using charge conservation\r\n\r\nCharge on $6 \\mu F$ capacitor $=\\frac{6}{6+4} \\times 30=18 \\mu C$\r\n\r\nSince charge is asked on right plate therefore is $+18 \\mu C$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39140,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>From the diagram of the circuit,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;are in series, so the total capacitance is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>'</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;are parallel, the total capacitance is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;are in series. So the equivalent capacitance is,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>2</mn></mstyle></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;F</mi></math></p><p>Using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mi>V</mi></math>.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d1ba759f-43cb-4ae0-b9ca-59765a1276c3.png\" style=\"width: 361px; height: 248px;\" /></p><p>The charge through the battery,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;From the diagram above,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#956;C</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39136,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Capacitance","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>All the capacitors are in parallel combination and therefore potential drop across each capacitor would be the same.</p><p>Charge on the capacitor can be written as,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></math>.</p><p>The charge on&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p><p>The charge on&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p><p>The charge on&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p><p>By the given data.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>10</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (15 Apr Shift 1)","image":null}]